dict.string: The Dock payload is designated by specifying com.apple.dock as the PayloadType. The Dock payload is supported on the user channel and, except for AllowDockFixupOverride, on all version of macOS. The key AllowDockFixupOverride is supported on macOS 10.12 and later.
The human-readable description of this payload. This description appears on the Detail screen.
The human-readable name for the profile payload. The name appears on the Detail screen and doesn't need to be unique.

The reverse-DNS-style identifier for the payload. This identifier is usually the same as the TopLevel value, with an additional appended component. This string must be unique within the profile. During a profile replacement, the system updates payloads with the same 'PayloadIdentifier' and 'PayloadUUID' in the old and new profiles.
The payload type, which each payload domain's reference page specifies.

The globally unique identifier for the payload. The actual content is unimportant, but must be globally unique. In macOS, use 'uuidgen' to generate UUIDs. During a profile replacement, the system updates payloads with the same 'PayloadIdentifier' and 'PayloadUUID' in the old and new profiles.
The version of this specific payload.
The human-readable string containing the name of the organization that provides the profile. This value doesn't need to match the organization payload value in the enclosing dictionary.
An array of items located on the Applications side of the Dock and cannot be removed from that location.
The type of the tile. Values may be file-tile, directory-tile, or url-tile. If you are unsure whether the file item is a file or a directory, set this key to file-tile.
Required. The type of the tile. Values may be file-tile, directory-tile, or url-tile. If you are unsure whether the file item is a file or a directory, set this key to file-tile.
Required. Information about a dock item.
Required. Label of a dock item.
Display name in the profile GUI of a dock item.
The type of the tile expressed as a number.
Required. The type of the tile expressed as a number. 3 = directory, 0 = URL, 1 = file.
pfm_type_input set to string to enable pfm_value_copy to work as expected.

The size of the largest magnification.
If 'true', enables 'Minimize windows into application icon.'
If 'true', disables the 'Minimize windows into application icon' checkbox.
Minimize windows into application icon Checkbox Disable
If 'true', enables 'Automatically hide and show the dock.'
Automatically hide and show the Dock

If true, shows the process indicator.

If 'true', uses the 'static-apps' and 'static-others' dictionaries for the dock and ignores any items in the 'persistent-apps' and 'persistent-others' dictionaries. If 'false', the contents are merged with the static items listed first.
Remove non-static apps and documents from Dock
If 'true', disables changes to the dock.

If 'true', use the file in '/Library/Preferences/com.apple.dockfixup.plist' when a new user or migrated user logs in. This option has no effect for existing users. Available in macOS 10.12 and later. Only available on the device channel.

One or more special folders that may be created at user login time and placed in the dock.
The 'My Applications' item is only used for Simple Finder environments. The 'Original Network Home' item is only used for mobile account users.
